The paper discusses machine learning-based detection and interpretation-based indirect knowledge transfer, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of activation maximization to generate visualizations also suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the goal of enabling sleep apnea monitoring and machine learning-based detection at home suggests a potential focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
